<!DOCTYPE.html>
<html>
<head>
<title> JavaScript Project 1</title>
</head>
<body>
<h3> <br> My First JavaScript enabled webpage</h3>
<p>
    This is an HTML webpage that has JavaScript embedded inside. <br/>
This will first test that JavaScript is enabled on this browser. <br/>
If it is, the script will format a large number with appropriate commas. <br/>
    If not, then a message will appear informing the user Javascript is not enabled.
    </p>
<hr>
    </body>
        
    
<script>
 

    document.write("JavaScript is enabled for this browser.<br/>")

  function formatNumber(num) {
return num.toString().replace(/(\d)(?=(\d{3})+(?!\d))/g, "$1,") }

    
    document.write("<br/>The number 987654321 formatted with commas is: <b> "+formatNumber(987654321)+"</b>"); 
   

    
    </script>
    

    <noscript>
             Nothing to see.
             <br/><br/>
             Java not enabled on this browser!
         </noscript>
    
    
    <hr>
    
    <p> The above was generated by the JavaScript code. <br/> 
    This is now back to HTML. <br/>
    We hope you enjoyed the demonstration. <br/>
    <br/> 
    [Enieda Baja] </p>
    
</html>
